commit.message:
Merge pull request #22 from vinpublic/master

Quite trivial fix of issue #21
Quite trivial fix of issue #21
Fix directory creation warning when we tell Epoch to shut up about it. Fixes #20
Add licensing info to readme
Update README.
Allow specifying build options for buildepoch.sh via makefile.
Allow DefinePriority=PriorityB PriorityA+1
Fix memory leak in 'epoch merge'.
Add 'epoch merge' and 'epoch unmerge' commands to make dealing with multiple config files much easier.
Add missing piece of logfile config option thingy.
Add support for specifying log file in the config file.
Add pseudo dependency support by allowing us to say ObjectStartPriority=udev+1 etc
Add interactive boot mode as promised, fixes #17
Implement /.epochnokargs file, fixes #18
Fix some comments.
Explain to users why InitMemBus() might fail when they see the error.
Fix help output a little bit.
Add statusnc command as a way to exclude color output in status command.
Add skipobj= and startobj= kernel cli options. Very useful.
Add a slightly useful make clean to our new makefile shim.
Make a huge leap and jump to C99.
Add shim Makefile that just calls ./buildepoch.sh
Change bootup version-printing format again.
Fix rather severe typo in ExecuteConfigObject() that steps outside memory lane.
Add option to specify auto-restart restarting-too-fast time.
Make the version announcement on boot less flashy
Add option to silently ignore when a MountVirtual filesystem fails to mount
Remove colors from help output to fix use with 'less' command
Fix segfault on attempting to use EditConfigValue() to edit a config file on a readonly filesystem.
Fix completely broken value written to config by objrl.
